<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-01-14T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-01-14T13:00:00-05:00" n="34" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d34">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">868.51 Struma Valley/2d: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Minister in Greece</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Skinner</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-01-14T13:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">January 14,
                                        1928—1 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>4. Department’s 2, January 12, 10 a.m. Department understands that
                            Monks-Ulen proposal is the only one from American concerns <pb facs="0142" n="32" xml:id="pg_32"/> for Struma Valley drainage. If
                            such is not the case you will of course bear in mind Department’s policy
                            of strict impartiality between competing American concerns.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Olds</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>